    public class StorageModuleActivity
extends DatabaseModuleActivity

    StorageModuleActivity

    In the order of ModuleActivities, this one is the fourth module which it handles Firebase storage. It uses Storage as an interface and the main job will be done in StorageImpl class. Unlike AuthenticationModuleActivity which it used interfaces to trigger value changes, this module tries to notify any changes using Rx BehaviorSubject. This Rx subject is created here, but it's not subscribed yet. so it's harmless! It gets subscribed in MainActivity and AddNewActivity and when its task is done, it will get disposed.
